text: Roderick "Rody" Falesca Renee Trygvae Rijnders (1 March 1941 â€“ 15 January 2018) was a Dutch coxswain. He was born in Batavia. He won the silver medal in the coxed pairs at the 1968 Summer Olympics, alongside Hadriaan van Nes and Herman Suselbeek, as well a European bronze in 1965. Rijnders died on 15 January 2018 in The Hague at the age of 76. ==References== Category:1941 births Category:2018 deaths Category:Olympic silver medalists for the Netherlands Category:Dutch rowers Category:People from Batavia
